noun.description: A person who or thing which does not combine or agree with another person or thing; a person who does not agree to or comply with the terms of a settlement, etc.; (English History) a member of that section of the Jacobite party (1692) which sought the restoration of James II without the imposition of any conditions.

origin: Mid 17th century; earliest use found in Noah Biggs (fl. 1651), medical practitioner and social reformer. From non- + compounder.
